%h1.page-header Popular Baby Names in the US, 1880-2014

%p
  This is a visualization and analysis of baby name popularity data from the #{link_to 'US Office of Social Security', 'http://www.ssa.gov/oact/babynames', target: '_blank'}. The data stretches back to 1880, although it's most reliable after 1937 (when Social Security actually began).

%p
  Parents put a lot of love and care into their choices of what names to give their children. This is a dataset, but it is
  also a reflection of familial love and hope; it is a record of the source of generations. As such, things that happen in the world,
  things that matter to people, are visible in it. This visualization aims to make those stories accessible.

